commit.message:
Switch to nose2 for testing and mild doc cleanup

The orignal Nose project is deprecated and vaguely unmaintained. Switch
to nose2, which is its successor.

Tag v0.15 and release.
Drop superfluous assignment of Exceptio object

Fix common code to always have a returncode

Since the return code is now explicitly check, make sure the attribute
is always defined. Also fix tests in line with that

Fix error handling of systemctl status process (#7)

* Fix error handling of systemctl status process

At least on one system using Python 3.8 the error output of `systemctl status
[pid]` would not be written to the output variable. Also the output of
systemctl (version 246) apparantly changed to

"Failed to get unit for PID [pid]: PID [pid] does not belong to any loaded
unit."

Therefore I think it is better to check the return code of the `systemctl status`
process and if it is non-zero, return None.

Fix error handling of systemctl status process (#7)

* Fix error handling of systemctl status process

At least on one system using Python 3.8 the error output of `systemctl status
[pid]` would not be written to the output variable. Also the output of
systemctl (version 246) apparantly changed to

"Failed to get unit for PID [pid]: PID [pid] does not belong to any loaded
unit."

Therefore I think it is better to check the return code of the `systemctl status`
process and if it is non-zero, return None.

commit.message:
Fix some Python 3 warnings and release v0.14

Hanno reported the unclosed FD warnings caused by me not using contexts
or explicit close() statements. Fix that.

Also fix some use of the deprecated assertEquals() method and autopep8
all py files.

Closes #6

Make permission warnings more useful

- print newline at end of PERMWARNING
- have PERMWARNINGUID0 be the warning printed for UID == 0
- have PERMWARNING be the warning printed for UID != 0

Contributed by Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org>
Version 0.13
Add anonymous hugepages pseudofile to blacklist
Acutally, v0.12
Version 0.11

Make warning about read errors more specific

This closes isse #4
Add tests for new i915 false positive
Add blacklist entry for X server on i915 DRM
Quodlibet has changed its orcexec path
Fix leftover debug message
Fall back to utf-8 if stdin has no encoding
Switch to using setuptools instead of mkdist
Typo fixes
Cleanups: make flake8 happy and switch to next version-#

Fix test suite for 2.7

While a bit heavy-handed, we can stub out the whole of sys.stderr
instead of just its write() method. That way, both 2.7 and 3.x are
happy.

Also, the mock submodule of unittest has been backported to 2.7, so we
can use that.

Fix the tests for 3.5/3.4

This unfortunately does not fix the problems with testing under 2.7.
fixed parameter names in docstring (#2)

Fix reading from process when using python3

In python3 the output returned by communicate() will be bytes which
cannot be checked if something is "in" it in the next line.

Move static pattern to dynamic

This is also used by e.g. pulseaudio and chrome:

5839;/memfd:pulseaudio;/opt/google/chrome-beta/chrome
--user-data-dir=/home/klausman/.config/google-chrome-beta
--extra-plugin-dir=/usr/lib64/nsbrowser/plugins
--extra-plugin-dir=/usr/lib64/nsbrowser/plugins
--extra-plugin-dir=/usr/lib64/nsbrowser/plugins
Merge githubification with other changes
Update for new tools
Github-ify the README and use MD
Github-ify the README and use MD

Add another no-lib pattern

This has started appearing with recent releases of X11/Mesa.

Protip: when you factor out stuff into a module...

... makes sure to actually include it in your next commit.
